      ' <p align="justify"><span><b>(1) </b>The <i>principal authority</i> that administers the <i>maintenance inspection program</i> established under Sentence 1.10.2.3.(1), may, as an alternative to conducting an inspection of a <i>sewage system</i> required under Sentence 1.10.2.3.(1), accept a certificate described in Sentence (2) from the owner of the property on which the <i>sewage system</i> is located.</span></p> <p align="justify"><span><b>(2) </b>The certificate required by Sentence (1) shall satisfy the requirements of Sentence 1.10.1.3.(2) and for these purposes Sentences 1.10.1.3.(3) to (5) apply with necessary modifications.</span></p> <p align="right"><span>O.&nbsp;Reg. 332/12, Division&nbsp;C, Part&nbsp;1; O. Reg. 151/13, ss. 38, 39; O. Reg. 361/13, ss.&nbsp;120-122; O. Reg. 191/14, ss.&nbsp;146-154; O.&nbsp;Reg. 332/12, Sentence 4.2.1.1.(4, 5); O. Reg. 139/17, ss. 147-152; O. Reg. 462/17, s. 3; O. Reg. 388/18, s. 3.</span></p> <p align="center"><span class="c1">Part 2<br> Alternative solutions, Disputes, rulings and interpretations</span></p> ',
